2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new web graph model and compares it with existing models, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the connectivity of web graphs, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SD (Software Development) - The paper proposes a new model for web graphs, which could be useful for software development related to web applications. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the behavior of web graphs, which is related to the impact of computers and technology on society.
